Job Description:
This job is for the 2023-2024 contract year

RRPS District Office- IT Department

240-day contract


Job Title: IT Data Engineer




Minimum Qualifications:

Associates Degree in Information Technology, Data Science, or a related field;
Minimum of 3 years’ experience with data, IT or a related field;
Proficiency in Python, SQL and other languages; and
Valid New Mexico Driver’s License.

Position Description:

The Data Engineer will be a pivotal link in the chain of data management, ensuring effective data interoperability across RRPS systems, including student information systems and various third-party systems. The engineer will focus on enhancing data accessibility and reliability, supporting data-driven decision-making across the District.


Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:

Knowledge of data management principles and data warehousing;
Proficiency in SQL for database querying and Python for data analysis and manipulation;
Experience with educational management systems, specifically PowerSchool;
Familiarity with Windows Servers and VMware vSphere;
Exceptional problem-solving and analytical abilities;
Solid understanding of database design, data modeling, and data integrity;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills;
Capacity to multitask, prioritize, and manage multiple projects simultaneously; and
Proficient in data visualization tools and techniques.

Essential Job Responsibilities:

Facilitate seamless data interoperability across Powerschool and other systems within the District, ensuring data consistency and integrity;
Provide tier 3 technical support for Versatrans transportation software, addressing import/export of data and complex technical challenges;
Maintain and manage a cloud-based Oracle database containing critical financial data;
Work with other cloud computing tools such as: Azure, Google Cloud or AWS;
Regularly collaborate with the network team, other IT teams, and various departments to facilitate data-driven decision-making and problem resolution;
Work with the Systems Administrator to improve systems processes and integrations;
Work to automate processes and improve systems performance and reliability;
Support data backup and retrieval procedures for district databases;
Analyze and evaluate current data systems, proposing and implementing improvements and enhancements;
Develop, implement, and enforce data standards and protocols to improve data quality, accessibility, and security;
Design and maintain data systems and databases; this includes fixing coding errors and other data-related problems;
Design and create data reports using various reporting tools to help the district make decisions;
Maintain technical documentation related to data management for reference and reporting;
Provide training and support to staff on data-related issues and tools;
Stay current with industry trends and advancements in data engineering and education technology;
Comply with state-approved New Mexico Administrative Code of Ethical Responsibility of the Education Profession and the RRPS Employee Standards of Conduct and upholds and enforces rules, administrative directives and regulations, school board policies, and local, state and federal regulations related to data management and privacy; and
Employee may be assigned other duties based on the needs of the district during the term of employment.

Work Hours: Work hours are established in employment contract. Additional work hours may be assigned by the Executive Director of Information Technology.


Accountability:

Reports to: Executive Director of Information Technology

Evaluated by: Executive Director of Information Technology


Application Procedure:

The following documents must be attached to complete this application:

One (1) transcript from each crediting college or university if not current in personnel file; and
Copy of valid New Mexico Driver's License.

An Equal Opportunity Employer


Minimum salary posted; final salary will be set based upon the minimum salary, education, and experience.
